      "content": "Apologies for the abrupt cut-off. Let's continue with replacing the washer and address the potential issue with a stuck stem.\n\n6. Replace the washer: If you need a new washer, you can usually find it at a hardware store. Make sure it's the correct size for your faucet. To replace the washer, simply unscrew it from the stem and then screw the new washer into place. Be sure to tighten it securely, but don't overtighten, as that could damage the washer or the stem.\n\nIf the stem is stuck and won't budge, don't worry. Here's what you can do:\n\n- Apply penetrating oil: Spray some penetrating oil (like WD-40) onto the stem and let it sit for a few minutes. This can help loosen any corrosion or debris that's causing the stem to stick.\n- Use gentle force: Try using a flathead screwdriver or a pair of pliers to gently wiggle the stem back and forth. Be careful not to apply too much force, as you don't want to break the stem.\n- Seek professional help: If the stem still won't budge, it might be time to call a professional plumber. They have the tools and expertise to handle stubborn issues without causing damage.\n\nI hope this helps you tackle",
